An Act establishing a standing commission on operating under the influence and impaired
driving.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 There shall be a standing commission on operating under the influence and impaired
2 driving established pursuant to section 2A of chapter 4 of the General Laws, referred to in this
3 section as the commission. The commission shall meet at least quarterly and shall review all
4 aspects of law enforcement personnel's ability to properly test impaired operators and prevent
5 impaired operation of motor vehicles and make any recommendations for improvements or
6 changes that the commission determines are necessary.
7 The commission shall consist of 13 members as follows: the secretary of public safety
8 and security or a designee, who shall serve as chair of the commission; the attorney general or a
9 designee; the colonel of the state police or a designee; the executive director of the
